## What I Worked On Today

Task A-6 requires the system owner and ISSO to prepare the POA&M for inclusion in the authorization package. The POA&M documents every open weakness with sufficient detail for the AO to understand: what the gap is, why it is not yet resolved, what the plan is to resolve it, who owns the plan, what the timeline is, and what compensating controls are in place while the gap remains open.

Today I work through each open item — the four assessment findings deferred to POA&M and the seven existing POA&M items — and produce complete, well-structured entries for each.

