### POA&M Item 003: Alternate Processing Site Test — CP-4

**Control Reference:** CP-4 (Contingency Plan Testing), CP-7 (Alternate Processing Site)

**Weakness Summary:** An alternate processing site arrangement exists (documented AWS alternate region configuration) but failover to the alternate site has not been tested. Quarterly restoration tests verify data recovery capability but test restoration to the primary region, not failover to the alternate region. The RMF High baseline requires testing that demonstrates the alternate processing capability is actually functional.

**Source:** Identified during Day 51; confirmed accurate by assessor.

**Risk Level:** Low (primary region recovery is tested and functional; alternate site gap is a redundancy assurance gap, not a primary recovery gap).

**Point of Contact:** IT Administrator (technical test), ISSO (documentation and coordination)

**Planned Milestones:**

| Milestone | Description | Target Date | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Document alternate site failover procedure as a testable procedure (specific steps, verification criteria) | [date + 30 days] | Open |
| 2 | Schedule alternate site failover test in a maintenance window | [date + 45 days] | Open |
| 3 | Execute alternate site failover test; document results including failover time and data integrity verification | [date + 60 days] | Open |
| 4 | POA&M item closed; results incorporated into contingency plan | [date + 75 days] | Open |

